olive oil
1 bunch Baby Broccoli
1 packet Asian Greens
2 clove Garlic
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
2 packet Beef Rump
1 packet Honey-Soy Sauce
1 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet coriander

• Trim baby broccoli.
• Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli lengthways.
• Roughly chop Asian greens.
• Finely chop garlic.
• Thinly slice fresh chilli.

• Place beef rump between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened. Season beef with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking.
• Transfer to a plate to rest.

TIP: Pounding the beef ensures that it's extra tender once cooked.
TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded.

• Wipe out frying pan then return to medim-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook baby broccoli, tossing, until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and garlic, and cook until slighlty wilted and fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• In a small heatproof bowl, microwave honey-soy sauce and the vinegar, in 30 second bursts, until warmed through. Stir through any steak resting juices.
• Slice steak.
• Divide honey-soy beef steak and green veg stir-fry between plates.
• Spoon over honey-soy sauce and tear over coriander.
• Sprinkle chilli (if using) to garnish. Enjoy!